# Reviewer — Project Conventions

## Domain & URLs

- Production domain: `reviewer.yet-to-be.com`
- Never hardcode `*.workers.dev` URLs in user-facing code or docs

## Architecture

Two-process split deployment:

| Layer | Runtime | Entrypoint | Hosted on |
|-------|---------|------------|-----------|
| Worker (ingress + static assets) | Cloudflare Workers | `src/worker.ts` | Cloudflare |
| Runner (heavy compute, VMs, AI) | Bun | `src/server.ts` | Railway |

Both share the same Hono app (`src/app.ts`). The Worker verifies GitHub webhooks and proxies to the Runner via `RUNNER_BASE_URL` + `RUNNER_SHARED_SECRET`.

## Frontend

- React 19 SPA in `frontend/src/`, built with Vite, served as static assets by the Worker
- **Component library**: `@base-ui/react` — prefer this over hand-rolling primitives
- **Icons**: `@phosphor-icons/react` — never inline SVGs unless explicitly told to
- **Styling**: CSS Modules (`.module.css`) with design tokens from `frontend/src/styles/tokens.css`
  - Never use inline styles — define everything via CSS classes
  - Prefer token variables (`var(--primary)`, `var(--radius)`) over raw values
- **Imports**: named imports at the top of file — no `React.useEffect`, no dynamic imports unless explicitly needed
- Light mode is the default color scheme

## Backend

- Hono framework, TypeScript, strict mode
- Two tsconfigs: root (`jsxImportSource: "hono/jsx"`) and `frontend/tsconfig.json` (`jsxImportSource: "react"`)
- D1 (Cloudflare) for persistence — migration-first approach, never push migrations without explicit approval
- FastVM for sandboxed VM execution
- OpenAI SDK for AI features (streaming via SSE)

## Database

- D1 migrations live in `migrations/`
- Always create a migration file — never apply schema changes directly
- Never run or push migrations unless explicitly asked

## Dev servers

- `bun run dev` — Bun runner on `:3000`
- `bun run dev:worker` — Wrangler Worker on `:8787`
- `bun run dev:ui` — Vite dev server on `:5173` (proxies `/api`, `/auth`, `/health`, `/webhooks` → `:8787`)
- `bun run cf:deploy` — builds UI + deploys Worker

## Code style

- Keep files focused — break out reusable code into separate modules
- Minimal comments — only explain non-obvious intent
- Exhaustive switch handling for TypeScript unions/enums
- No dev-setup hints or config diagnostics in production UI — handle missing config silently or fail at the API level
